com.ppm.integration.agilesdk.agiledata

Class AgileDataIntegration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ppm.integration.agilesdk.agiledata.AgileDataIntegration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FunctionIntegration

    public abstract class AgileDataIntegration
extends java.lang.Object
implements FunctionIntegration
    Main class of Agile Data integration point, used to import agile information from the agile tool into PPM and use it for Dashboard reporting.
    A same instance of this class will be reused to import information from different projects, with the method setUp(ValueSet, String) being called between each project to pass the project ID of the next project.

    These integrations will be leveraged by the PPM "Agile Data Sync Service".
    Since:
    PPM9.42

      • setUp

        public abstract void setUp(ValueSet instanceConfiguration,
                           java.lang.String projectId)
        Initializes the connector with the configuration information. This method will be called once for each agile project before starting to retrieve the Agile Data for that agile project.
        Parameters:
        instanceConfiguration - the values of the configuration fields for the Connector
        projectId - the id of the project for which data is about to be retrieved.

      • getAgileDataBacklogConfig

        public abstract java.util.List<AgileDataBacklogConfig> getAgileDataBacklogConfig(ValueSet paramValueSet)
        Get the configuration on how the Backlog items should be displayed in the PPM portlets, i.e. which color should be used depending on the backlog item and its status.
        This method will be called when creating a new connector instance, NOT when synchronizing the Agile Data. So setUp(ValueSet, String) will not be called beforehand.
        See Also:
        AgileDataBacklogConfig
